tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated creatinine and chloride, suggesting possible renal impairment or dehydration. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, glucosuria, ketonuria, proteinuria) may indicate renal dysfunction, metabolic disturbance, or possible infection, though nitrites and leukocytes are negative. Low HbA1c with normal glucose is unusual and may warrant further investigation. HDL cholesterol is slightly low. Recommend clinical correlation and further renal and metabolic assessment.
